ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

06:04.451 --> 06:05.800
GET A POCKET MASK!

06:05.930 --> 06:07.367
THERE'S NO TIME!
-CAROLINE!

06:07.497 --> 06:09.064
-WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH YOU? KEEP GOING!

06:09.194 --> 06:13.851
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

06:15.853 --> 06:19.988
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.731
-[COUGHING]
-CAROLINE: OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

06:24.253 --> 06:25.689
YOU'RE OKAY.

06:28.126 --> 06:29.911
-GET AWAY FROM ME!

06:30.041 --> 06:32.217
-IT'S ALL RIGHT, WE'RE ONLY
TRYING TO HELP YOU, IT'S OKAY.

06:33.567 --> 06:35.830
-IT'S YOUR HELP THAT
ALMOST DROWNED ME.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.440
-LISTEN TO ME, YOU
WERE STRUGGLING.

06:37.571 --> 06:38.833
IT WAS OUR JOB TO MAKE
SURE THAT YOU GOT BACK

06:38.963 --> 06:39.877
TO SHORE SAFELY.

06:40.008 --> 06:41.705
-[SHALLOW BREATHING]

06:41.836 --> 06:44.229
IF I CAN'T MAKE IT
BACK TO SHORE ON MY OWN,

06:45.666 --> 06:47.798
THEN I DON'T WANT
TO MAKE IT AT ALL.

06:50.627 --> 06:53.587
[COUGHING]

06:55.545 --> 06:58.243
-WELL, WE CAN GIVE YOU
A RIDE! WAIT A MINUTE!

06:58.374 --> 06:59.723
-LET HIM GO.

06:59.854 --> 07:00.942
-WHAT THE HELL IS
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

07:01.072 --> 07:02.552
WHY DID YOU TRY AND PULL ME AWAY

07:02.683 --> 07:03.901
WHEN I WAS GIVING
HIM MOUTH TO MOUTH?

07:04.032 --> 07:05.686
-I TOLD YOU TO
USE A POCKET MASK!

07:05.816 --> 07:07.862
-I DIDN'T HAVE ONE,
LOGAN, AND NEITHER DID YOU!

07:07.992 --> 07:09.733
MY GOD, THERE WASN'T
TIME! HE COULD'VE DIED!

07:09.864 --> 07:11.213
-CAROLINE!

07:12.170 --> 07:13.998
HE HAS AIDS.

07:14.695 --> 07:19.439
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

07:27.316 --> 07:28.752
-HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

07:29.449 --> 07:31.842
-THAT IS RON 'BAD
BOY' PURCELL.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.236
HE WON THE DECATHLON.

07:34.366 --> 07:37.282
HE WAS A WORLD CLASS
ATHLETE AND WOMANIZER.

07:38.283 --> 07:40.024
IT WAS ALL OVER THE PRESS.

07:41.025 --> 07:43.680
HE LOST HIS ENDORSEMENTS,
HIS GIRLFRIEND LEFT HIM,

07:43.811 --> 07:46.466
AND HE GOT SUSPENDED BY THE UIC.

07:48.511 --> 07:50.861
I HEARD HE WAS MOVING
HERE FROM FLORIDA.

07:55.953 --> 07:58.042
CAROLINE--
-JUST DON'T.

08:11.795 --> 08:15.103
-TRACY: I LOVE YOU,
MITCH, I'LL ALWAYS LOVE YOU.

08:15.233 --> 08:17.018
-MITCH: DON'T EVER
LEAVE ME, TRACY.

08:17.148 --> 08:19.063
-TRACY: I WON'T.

08:19.977 --> 08:21.762
-HEY, DAD, WHY DON'T
YOU COME IN HERE?

08:21.892 --> 08:23.546
YOU'RE MISSING A
REALLY GOOD GAME.

08:23.677 --> 08:26.157
KIRALY AND STEFFES AGAINST
SINJIN SMITH AND STOKLOS.

08:26.288 --> 08:27.985
-ANNOUNCER: STEFFES ON TWO.

08:28.116 --> 08:30.248
SIDE AIM, WIDE AND STEP.

08:30.945 --> 08:34.208
-AW, MAN, SINJIN JUST MADE
THE AWESOMEST DIG IN SPIKE.

08:38.299 --> 08:39.693
-WHAT'S THE SCORE?

08:39.823 --> 08:42.086
-IT'S AT MATCH POINT.
KIRALY IS SERVING.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.959
-ANNOUNCER: SECOND
ATTEMPT. SERVE TO STOKLOS.

08:45.089 --> 08:47.570
-OH, YEAH! DID YOU SEE THAT?

08:48.310 --> 08:50.573
-YEAH, SINJIN'S GREAT, HUH?

08:52.575 --> 08:54.185
-ACTUALLY, HE JUST LOST.

08:54.316 --> 08:56.492
-[LAUGHS] OH.

08:57.319 --> 08:59.016
SORRY, PAL, I MISSED IT.

08:59.756 --> 09:01.236
I GUESS I WASN'T
PAYING ATTENTION.

09:01.366 --> 09:02.498
-NO PROBLEM.

09:03.194 --> 09:04.979
I TAPED IT, YOU
CAN WATCH IT AGAIN.

09:05.109 --> 09:07.068
-NO, NO, NO, IT'S
BEDTIME FOR YOU.

09:07.198 --> 09:08.460
YOU GOT SCHOOL TOMORROW, PAL.

09:09.679 --> 09:10.724
-ALL RIGHT.

09:12.334 --> 09:13.814
GOODNIGHT, DAD.

09:13.944 --> 09:15.598
-WHAT? NO ARGUMENT?

09:15.729 --> 09:18.209
-NO, I GOT A BIG TEST TOMORROW.

09:18.340 --> 09:19.689
I SHOULD GO TO BED.

09:21.038 --> 09:22.474
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

09:23.214 --> 09:24.868
-I LOVE YOU, TOO, PAL.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.177
-MAN: OKAY,
HOBIE FROM VENICE BEACH,

09:29.307 --> 09:31.179
TURN YOUR RADIO
DOWN, YOU'RE ON NEXT.

09:34.225 --> 09:36.097
-WOMAN: AND OUR
NEXT CALLER IS HOBIE

09:36.227 --> 09:37.707
FROM VENICE BEACH.

09:37.838 --> 09:40.188
WHAT'S YOUR LOVE PROBLEM, HOBIE?

09:41.189 --> 09:42.756
-HI. UM--

09:43.495 --> 09:45.454
WELL, IT'S NOT MY PROBLEM.

09:47.369 --> 09:50.241
I GUESS IT IS, BUT I'M
CALLING ABOUT MY DAD.

09:51.286 --> 09:52.548
-WOMAN: WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:52.679 --> 09:54.202
-WELL...

09:55.159 --> 09:58.510
SEE, MY DAD FELL IN LOVE
WITH THIS REALLY GREAT LADY,

09:59.599 --> 10:01.862
BUT SIX MONTHS AGO SHE DIED

10:03.777 --> 10:07.563
AND EVER SINCE, HE JUST
HASN'T GOTTEN OVER IT.

10:08.477 --> 10:10.174
-WOMAN: AND
YOU'RE FEELING HELPLESS?

10:11.132 --> 10:14.309
-YEAH, I MEAN, MY
DAD'S A LIFEGUARD

10:14.439 --> 10:18.792
AND HE'S USED TO SAVING PEOPLE
AND HELPING EVERYBODY ELSE.

10:19.444 --> 10:23.492
BUT, NOW HE NEEDS HELP AND
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

10:23.623 --> 10:26.060
-WOMAN: YOU SOUND LIKE
A VERY CARING PERSON, HOBIE,

10:26.190 --> 10:29.803
WHO LOVES HIS DAD A LOT.
IT MIGHT TAKE AWHILE

10:29.933 --> 10:33.154
FOR HIM TO LET YOUR LOVE
AND THE LOVE OF HIS FRIENDS

10:33.284 --> 10:36.766
HELP THE HEALING PROCESS,
SO JUST HANG IN THERE.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.246
-HOBIE: I JUST THOUGHT
THAT IF HE MET SOMEONE

10:38.376 --> 10:41.597
GREAT LIKE TRACY, IT'D HELP.

10:42.554 --> 10:44.165
-WOMAN: YEAH, IT MIGHT.

10:44.295 --> 10:46.341
FALLING IN LOVE IS
A POWERFUL FORCE

10:46.471 --> 10:49.257
THAT CAN BREAK OUR
HEARTS AND MEND THEM.

10:49.387 --> 10:51.563
HOBIE, I'M GOING TO
TAKE YOU OFF THE AIR

10:51.694 --> 10:53.217
AND GET YOUR ADDRESS.

10:53.348 --> 10:54.697
I WANNA SEND YOU AND
YOUR DAD SOME INFORMATION

10:54.828 --> 10:56.307
THAT MIGHT HELP, OKAY?

10:56.438 --> 10:57.657
-HOBIE: OKAY.

11:06.796 --> 11:08.145
-OKAY, READY? HERE WE GO.

11:08.276 --> 11:10.582
WALK AND AROUND,
WALK, GOOD. TURN OUT.

11:10.713 --> 11:12.802
TURN OUT, THAT'S
IT AND IN. GOOD.

11:12.933 --> 11:14.674
THAT'S ALL RIGHT, LOOK AT
ME, LOOK AT ME, LOOK AT ME.

11:14.804 --> 11:17.198
STRAIGHTEN YOUR ARM.
TURN OUT AND BACK.

11:17.328 --> 11:20.331
TURN OUT, GOOD, IN, DOWN.

11:20.462 --> 11:21.463
LOOK AT ME, LOOK AT ME.

11:21.593 --> 11:23.378
GOOD, DON'T LOSE EYE CONTACT.

11:23.508 --> 11:26.207
TURN OUT, BACK IN, RIGHT LEG UP.

11:26.337 --> 11:28.252
GOOD, GOOD, GOOD, GOOD,
GOOD. THAT'S PRETTY GOOD.

11:28.383 --> 11:30.167
GOOD, VERY GOOD, C.J.

11:30.298 --> 11:33.518
UP AND DIP, THAT'S
IT, DIPPING AROUND.

11:33.649 --> 11:36.434
UP AND AGAIN. DOWN AND UP.

11:37.522 --> 11:39.176
REAL SLOW, SLOW,
SLOW, SLOW, SLOW.

11:39.307 --> 11:40.961
READY, UP.

11:42.484 --> 11:45.661
-WOW, THAT IS AMAZING.
I'VE NEVER FELT SO FREE.

11:45.792 --> 11:47.358
-WELL, YOU LOOK LIKE A PRISONER

11:47.489 --> 11:49.404
WITH HER ANKLES TIED TOGETHER.

11:49.534 --> 11:50.797
-SHUT UP, TINA.

11:50.927 --> 11:53.190
-GO TO HELL, ANGELO.

11:54.801 --> 11:56.367
-WHO WAS THAT?

11:56.498 --> 11:59.544
-MY EX-PARTNER. SHE'S
JUST JEALOUS, THAT'S ALL.

11:59.675 --> 12:01.024
DON'T WORRY ABOUT HER.

12:01.155 --> 12:02.678
-WELL, YOU GUYS WON THE
CHAMPIONSHIP TWO YEARS

12:02.809 --> 12:05.028
IN A ROW, I'M NEVER
GONNA BE AS GOOD AS THAT.

12:05.159 --> 12:07.552
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT
IT, I'LL BE LEADING YOU

12:07.683 --> 12:09.424
AND EVERYBODY WILL BE
WATCHING ME ANYWAY.

12:10.381 --> 12:13.558
OKAY, OKAY, LET'S GO FROM
WHERE WE WERE. HERE WE GO.

12:13.689 --> 12:17.127
HERE. READY, WALK,
AROUND, AROUND.

12:17.258 --> 12:19.086
GOOD, TURN OUT,
TURN OUT, THAT'S IT,

12:19.216 --> 12:20.087
A LITTLE MORE, THAT'S IT.

12:20.740 --> 12:23.133
-OH, SORRY.
-MAN: THAT'S OKAY.

12:23.264 --> 12:25.222
-MITCH: NO, NO, TOWER
18 IS UNACCESSIBLE.

12:25.353 --> 12:27.007
THERE'S TOO MANY DRIFTS.

12:29.444 --> 12:31.054
UH...

12:31.185 --> 12:32.577
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.101
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

12:34.231 --> 12:35.493
-LETTERS FOR YOU.

12:35.624 --> 12:36.494
-[CHUCKLING]

12:37.626 --> 12:38.670
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

12:38.801 --> 12:39.976
I DON'T KNOW ANY
OF THESE PEOPLE.

12:40.107 --> 12:42.022
-THE RADIO STATION
SENT THEM OVER.

12:45.590 --> 12:46.896
-WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN UP TO?

12:48.028 --> 12:50.465
-I JUST CALLED A TALK
SHOW AND TOLD THEM

12:50.595 --> 12:51.771
HOW WORRIED I WAS ABOUT YOU.

12:54.338 --> 12:57.037
-YOU TALKED ABOUT MY
PERSONAL LIFE ON THE RADIO?

12:57.167 --> 12:59.300
-ALL I SAID WAS WHAT
A GREAT GUY YOU WERE

12:59.430 --> 13:01.519
AND HOW SAD YOU'VE BEEN LATELY.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.958
NOW ALL THESE LADIES
WANNA CHEER YOU UP.

13:05.959 --> 13:07.830
-LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE
TRYING TO HELP, PAL,

13:08.570 --> 13:11.051
BUT NONE OF THESE PEOPLE
CAN REPLACE TRACY.

13:11.834 --> 13:15.969
-I KNOW THAT. DON'T YOU
EVEN WANT TO READ THEM?

13:16.839 --> 13:17.840
-NO.

13:41.081 --> 13:43.474
-HI.
-OH, HI.

13:44.127 --> 13:45.259
-WHAT'S ALL THIS ABOUT?

13:46.260 --> 13:48.044
-THEY'RE FROM WOMEN
WHO WANT TO MEET MY DAD.

13:48.175 --> 13:49.524
I'M SCREENING THEM FOR HIM.

13:50.177 --> 13:52.005
-MITCH PUT AN AD
IN THE PERSONALS?

13:52.135 --> 13:53.833
THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE HIM.

13:53.963 --> 13:56.836
-ACTUALLY, IT WAS
A RADIO TALK SHOW

13:56.966 --> 13:58.663
AND IT WASN'T HIM, IT WAS ME.

13:59.186 --> 14:02.798
I CALLED IN FOR ADVICE AND
THE LETTERS JUST POURED IN.

14:03.451 --> 14:05.932
-DEAR MITCH, I AM
A REGISTERED NURSE

14:06.062 --> 14:08.195
WHO PRACTICES MASSAGE THERAPY.

14:09.239 --> 14:11.459
I CAN EASE YOUR PAIN?

14:12.416 --> 14:13.765
YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME.

14:13.896 --> 14:15.593
-WELL, SOME OF THEM
ARE KIND OF LAME.

14:16.159 --> 14:17.378
-KIND OF?

14:19.162 --> 14:21.861
WHOA, THIS IS REALLY
GONNA GET HIS ATTENTION.

14:21.991 --> 14:25.342
-WHAT'S THAT?
-AH! I DON'T THINK SO,
SHE'S NOT YOUR DAD'S TYPE.

14:25.473 --> 14:27.997
YOU KNOW, I THINK I SHOULD
HELP YOU WITH THESE.

14:28.563 --> 14:30.521
-YEAH, I DO, TOO,
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

14:39.661 --> 14:40.705
WOW.

14:41.619 --> 14:45.710
THIS IS IT. THIS IS
THE ONE, I KNOW IT.

14:48.322 --> 14:49.845
-STEPHANIE: DEAR HOBIE,
I KNOW YOU'RE WORRIED

14:49.976 --> 14:51.325
ABOUT YOUR DAD AND WITH
ALL THE LOVE THAT YOU HAVE

14:51.455 --> 14:53.196
TO GIVE HIM, I KNOW
HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

14:53.327 --> 14:54.763
I MADE THIS FOR
YOU TO GIVE TO HIM,

14:54.894 --> 14:55.938
WHENEVER I'VE BEEN LOST,
IT'S ALWAYS HELPED ME

14:56.069 --> 14:57.897
TO FIND THE WAY, CALLIE.

14:58.680 --> 15:02.031
-WOW, THE PICTURE
EVEN LOOKS LIKE US.

15:02.684 --> 15:04.642
-WELL, MAYBE IT'S
SOMEONE WHO KNOWS YOU.

15:05.339 --> 15:06.644
-LET'S SEE.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.647
NOPE, SHE LIVES IN SAN DIEGO.

15:11.127 --> 15:12.346
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE IN HERE.

15:16.045 --> 15:17.438
-HEY, LET'S SEE WHAT SHE SENT.

15:17.568 --> 15:20.310
-OH, NO, I THINK MY
DAD SHOULD OPEN IT.

15:21.007 --> 15:22.269
SHE MADE IT FOR HIM.

15:24.140 --> 15:25.141
-STEPHANIE: OKAY.

15:28.710 --> 15:30.799
-HOBIE: HEY, DAD.
-HMM?

15:31.408 --> 15:33.062
-GOT SOMETHING FOR YOU.

15:34.324 --> 15:35.282
-WHAT IS IT?

15:37.371 --> 15:40.200
-IT'S FOR YOU. A
FRIEND OF MINE MADE IT.

15:43.768 --> 15:45.118
GO AHEAD, OPEN IT.

15:52.952 --> 15:55.998
-MITCH: WOW, BEAUTIFUL.

15:56.129 --> 15:58.131
-HOBIE: CHECK OUT THE
COMPASS NEXT TO THE CLOCK.

16:00.002 --> 16:01.047
-WHAT'S THIS FOR?

16:01.873 --> 16:05.225
-I GUESS IT'S TO HELP YOU
FIND YOUR WAY WHEN YOU'RE LOST.

16:07.444 --> 16:09.272
-WELL, I HAVE TO THANK
YOUR FRIEND WHO MADE THIS.

16:09.403 --> 16:10.578
WHO IS IT?

16:11.579 --> 16:14.277
-SOMEONE NEW, WANNA MEET HER?

16:14.408 --> 16:15.931
-YEAH, SURE.

16:16.584 --> 16:17.715
-GREAT.

16:23.939 --> 16:27.203
SAN DIEGO, THE NUMBER
FOR CALLIE PHILLIPS.

16:28.726 --> 16:32.078
-[PHONE BUTTONS BEEPING]

16:32.208 --> 16:34.254
[PHONE RINGING]

16:34.384 --> 16:35.255
-HELLO?

16:35.385 --> 16:36.952
-HI, IS THIS CALLIE?

16:37.083 --> 16:40.564
-HOBIE, HELLO, HOW ARE YOU?

16:40.695 --> 16:42.610
-HOW'D YOU KNOW IT WAS ME?

16:42.740 --> 16:44.699
-I RECOGNIZE YOUR VOICE.

16:45.482 --> 16:47.615
-DO WE KNOW YOU BECAUSE
THE PICTURE YOU DREW

16:47.745 --> 16:49.660
OF ME AND MY DAD
LOOKS EXACTLY LIKE US.

16:49.791 --> 16:51.967
-GREAT, I WAS HOPING IT WOULD.

16:52.098 --> 16:54.535
-SO, WE DON'T KNOW YOU?

16:55.362 --> 16:56.928
-THAT WAS JUST THE
IMAGE THAT CAME TO ME

16:57.059 --> 16:58.408
WHEN I WAS LISTENING
TO YOU TALK.

16:59.061 --> 17:00.671
HOW'S YOUR DAD FEELING?

17:00.802 --> 17:03.413
-PRETTY GOOD, HE LOVED
THE PRESENT YOU SENT HIM.

17:03.544 --> 17:04.588
IT WAS REALLY COOL.

17:04.719 --> 17:06.286
-I HOPE IT HELPS.

17:06.415 --> 17:09.593
-SO, DO YOU EVER COME
UP TO LOS ANGELES?

17:10.246 --> 17:11.682
-OCCASIONALLY ON BUSINESS.

17:11.813 --> 17:13.944
-OH, GREAT, THEN
YOU CAN MEET MY DAD.

17:15.382 --> 17:17.079
-THAT'S NOT WHY I
WROTE YOU, HOBIE.

17:17.949 --> 17:18.776
-IT'S NOT?

17:19.560 --> 17:21.910
-I JUST WANTED TO
SEND YOU BOTH A BIG HUG

17:22.040 --> 17:23.867
AND LET YOU KNOW THAT
IT'LL ALL BE OKAY.

17:25.174 --> 17:27.481
I'VE BEEN THERE IN
YOUR DAD'S SHOES

17:28.743 --> 17:31.528
AND AS LONG AS HE HAS
YOU, IT'LL BE JUST FINE.

17:31.659 --> 17:33.878
-BUT, CALLIE, YOU
HAVE TO MEET MY DAD.

17:34.009 --> 17:35.750
I WANNA MEET YOU, TOO, I MEAN,

17:36.403 --> 17:37.708
CAN'T YOU JUST COME FOR A VISIT?

17:38.361 --> 17:40.102
-I'D LOVE TO MEET
YOU AND YOUR DAD--

17:40.233 --> 17:43.323
-GREAT, THEN YOU CAN MEET
US ON THE SANTA MONICA PIER,

17:43.453 --> 17:46.630
4:00 ON SATURDAY, WE'LL
BE ON THE FERRIS WHEEL.

17:47.979 --> 17:49.503
-ON THE FERRIS WHEEL.

17:52.723 --> 17:54.290
4:00 SATURDAY.

17:54.421 --> 17:55.596
-ALL RIGHT.

17:55.726 --> 17:58.207
-AND HOBIE?
-YEAH?

17:59.339 --> 18:02.081
-YOUR DAD'S REALLY LUCKY
TO HAVE A PAL LIKE YOU.

18:02.211 --> 18:04.431
-THANKS, BYE.

18:05.171 --> 18:06.346
-BYE, BYE.

18:20.534 --> 18:22.666
-[MELLOW MUSIC]

18:23.450 --> 18:24.712
-PASTA IS READY.

18:24.842 --> 18:26.409
-OKAY, IN A MINUTE.

18:36.680 --> 18:38.117
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:38.247 --> 18:39.988
-YOU'LL SEE WHEN I'M FINISHED.

18:40.119 --> 18:41.816
-COME ON, WHAT IS IT? IS IT
SOME SORT OF PRACTICAL JOKE?

18:41.946 --> 18:43.426
-THIS IS NO JOKE.

18:43.557 --> 18:44.949
-WELL, THEN, WHAT IS IT?

18:45.080 --> 18:47.169
-WELL, IT'S CALLED A
RESCUE CAN, CAROLINE

18:47.300 --> 18:49.084
AND IT'S DESIGNED TO SAVE LIVES.

18:49.215 --> 18:52.957
LET'S JUST SAY,
I'M REDESIGNING IT.

18:53.088 --> 18:55.351
-WELL, I SAY THAT
IT'S GONNA HAVE TO WAIT

18:56.352 --> 19:00.530
BECAUSE THE PASTA'S GONNA
GET COLD, BUT I'M NOT.

19:18.287 --> 19:20.246
WHY DID YOU JUST
PULL AWAY FROM ME?

19:20.376 --> 19:22.291
-I'M IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

19:25.729 --> 19:27.122
-THAT'S NOT IT.

19:32.475 --> 19:34.434
YOU DON'T WANNA KISS ME
BECAUSE I GAVE MOUTH TO MOUTH

19:34.564 --> 19:35.696
TO A MAN WITH AIDS.

19:35.826 --> 19:37.132
-THAT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

19:38.133 --> 19:41.136
-YOU CAN'T GET AIDS FROM
MOUTH TO MOUTH CONTACT, LOGAN.

19:41.267 --> 19:44.661
-OH, NO? WHAT IF YOU CUT
HIS LIP WITH YOUR TOOTH?

19:44.792 --> 19:45.749
TRYING TO GET A GOOD SEAL.

19:45.880 --> 19:47.186
-BUT, I DIDN'T.

19:47.316 --> 19:49.057
-WELL, YOU COULD HAVE.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.450
THAT'S WHY WE SHOULD
HAVE POCKET MASKS

19:50.580 --> 19:52.408
WITH US AT ALL TIMES.

19:52.539 --> 19:56.020
WE PRACTICE SAFE SEX, WE
SHOULD PRACTICE SAFE CPR.

19:57.152 --> 19:57.979
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

19:58.109 --> 19:59.633
-EXCUSE ME.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.418
WHAT ABOUT THE DINNER?

20:02.549 --> 20:05.508
-I'M NOT HUNGRY. SEE
YOU IN THE MORNING.

20:07.380 --> 20:10.687
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

20:22.525 --> 20:24.353
-EXCUSE ME, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO PUT THAT OUT.

20:25.572 --> 20:27.356
THERE'S NO FIRE ALLOWED ON THE--

20:30.794 --> 20:32.187
ON THE BEACH.

20:36.017 --> 20:37.671
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
THIS TIME? ARREST ME?

20:43.198 --> 20:44.373
-WHY ARE YOU BURNING
ALL THIS STUFF?

20:45.200 --> 20:47.202
-'CAUSE IT'S ALL IT'S GOOD FOR.

20:50.379 --> 20:51.902
-IS THAT A PICTURE
OF YOUR FAMILY?

20:53.730 --> 20:55.254
-ONCE UPON A TIME.

21:01.869 --> 21:03.827
-HOW CAN YOU JUST
BURN IT LIKE THAT?

21:05.046 --> 21:07.266
-I'M SURE THEY BURNED
MINE A LONG TIME AGO.

21:16.623 --> 21:18.407
-I'M SORRY ABOUT WHAT
HAPPENED THE OTHER DAY.

21:19.147 --> 21:21.105
-DON'T LET IT HAPPEN AGAIN.

21:22.411 --> 21:24.326
-DON'T TRY ANY MORE BUOY SWIMS.

21:24.457 --> 21:27.329
-I'M A PRO ATHLETE,
I'VE SWAM FROM HERE

21:27.460 --> 21:29.244
TO CATALINA AND BACK.

21:30.289 --> 21:32.116
AND THE DAY I CAN'T
MAKE A BUOY SWIM,

21:33.204 --> 21:34.858
I'D RATHER DROWN.

21:40.124 --> 21:42.997
-LOOK, I DON'T
PRETEND TO UNDERSTAND

21:43.127 --> 21:47.262
WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH,
BUT TO PUT YOUR LIFE AT RISK

21:47.393 --> 21:48.872
TO PROVE SOME SORT OF
A POINT, I'M SORRY,

21:49.003 --> 21:50.918
THAT JUST CAN'T BE THE ANSWER.

21:51.048 --> 21:53.181
-WHAT IS? HANGING ON
UNTIL I CAN BARELY WALK?

21:53.312 --> 21:55.966
-THE LONGER YOU STAY ALIVE,
THE BETTER THE CHANCES ARE

21:56.097 --> 21:57.707
THAT THEY'LL FIND A
TREATMENT FOR AIDS.

21:58.273 --> 21:59.492
THEY CAN EVEN FIND A CURE.

21:59.622 --> 22:01.494
-YEAH, YOU'RE
RIGHT, THEY COULD.

22:02.190 --> 22:04.410
IF ALL THE DOCTORS AND THE
SCIENTISTS, AND THE POLITICIANS

22:04.540 --> 22:06.020
AND THE DRUG COMPANIES
WILL WORK TOGETHER

22:06.150 --> 22:07.500
INSTEAD OF COMPETING
TO SEE WHO'S GOING

22:07.630 --> 22:09.589
TO MAKE THAT BIG SCORE.

22:12.243 --> 22:13.810
UNTIL PEOPLE BECOME MORE
IMPORTANT THAN MONEY,

22:13.941 --> 22:15.551
I AIN'T HOLDING MY BREATH.

22:16.639 --> 22:21.688
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

22:31.175 --> 22:33.134
-MAN: LIFEGUARD!

22:33.264 --> 22:35.136
LIFEGUARD!

22:35.266 --> 22:36.964
LIFEGUARD!

22:38.531 --> 22:40.707
DO YOU GOT ANYTHING
FOR A WETTY RASH?

22:41.490 --> 22:42.491
-SURE.

22:43.100 --> 22:45.407
-IT REALLY HURTS.
-C.J.: HOLD ON.

22:46.582 --> 22:47.801
YOU KNOW YOU SHOULD
WEAR A RASH GUARD

22:47.931 --> 22:49.237
UNDERNEATH YOUR WETSUIT.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.935
-I KNOW, BUT MINE
GOT REALLY GNARLY

22:52.066 --> 22:55.548
AND I KEPT SPITTING UP MILK.

22:55.678 --> 22:56.940
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:57.071 --> 22:59.073
-AREN'T YOU GOING
TO RUB IT ON ME?

22:59.203 --> 23:00.466
-I THINK YOU'VE BEEN
THROUGH THE RINSE CYCLE

23:00.596 --> 23:01.597
TOO MANY TIMES.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.469
PUT IT BACK WHEN YOU'RE DONE.

23:12.826 --> 23:15.481
-OH, C.J., REMEMBER YOU'VE
GOTTA GET HIM TO THE PIER

23:15.611 --> 23:17.221
BY 4:00.

23:17.352 --> 23:19.180
-I WILL.
-AND MAKE SURE HE
WEARS HIS DRESS UNIFORM.

23:19.310 --> 23:20.964
-IT'S AS GOOD AS DONE.

23:21.095 --> 23:24.315
THIS IS SO ROMANTIC, IT'S
LIKE SLEEPLESS IN SEATTLE.

23:25.099 --> 23:26.405
YOU MUST'VE SEEN IT?

23:26.535 --> 23:28.494
-A ROMANTIC MOVIE,
I DON'T THINK SO.

23:28.624 --> 23:31.584
-HOBIE, WHAT YOU'RE
DOING IS ROMANTIC.

23:31.714 --> 23:33.977
WOMEN LOVE ROMANTIC MEN.

23:36.763 --> 23:38.634
DON'T GROW OUT OF IT.

23:42.333 --> 23:44.379
DIP ME!
-MITCH: WHAT?

23:44.510 --> 23:46.425
-I NEED TO SEE IF I'M
GONNA DIP OUT OF MY DRESS.

23:46.555 --> 23:48.122
-C.J., I'M ALL SWEATY HERE.

23:48.252 --> 23:49.602
-SO ARE ALL THE MEN
I DANCE WITH.

23:50.733 --> 23:51.908
NOW DIP ME.

23:54.694 --> 23:55.738
DID ANYTHING SHOW?

23:55.869 --> 23:56.957
-I WASN'T LOOKING.

23:57.087 --> 23:58.741
-YOU HAVE TO LOOK AND TELL ME.

23:58.872 --> 24:00.656
I DON'T WANT TO BE EMBARRASSED
IN THE DANCE CONTEST.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.790
-AH! EVERYTHING'S
IN PLACE, OKAY?

24:03.920 --> 24:06.706
-OKAY, GOOD.
OKAY, THE CONTEST STARTS
AT 4:00 AND DON'T BE LATE.

24:06.836 --> 24:08.229
EVERYONE'S WEARING
DRESS UNIFORMS.

24:08.359 --> 24:09.709
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT? WAIT, WAIT.

24:09.839 --> 24:11.232
-WELL, YOU'RE
COMING, AREN'T YOU?

24:11.362 --> 24:13.103
-WELL, NO, C.J. I
WASN'T PLANNING ON IT.

24:14.191 --> 24:18.326
-[CRIES] IT'S SUCH
A BIG DAY FOR ME.

24:18.457 --> 24:20.807
I'VE BEEN REHEARSING SO HARD.

24:20.937 --> 24:22.548
EVERYONE'S GONNA BE THERE.

24:22.678 --> 24:24.767
-LET'S JUST STOP--
STOP CRYING ALL RIGHT?

24:24.898 --> 24:27.422
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, HELLO?

24:27.553 --> 24:28.597
I'LL BE THERE, I'LL
BE THERE, OKAY?

24:28.728 --> 24:31.295
-GOOD, WEAR YOUR DRESS UNIFORM.

24:32.166 --> 24:35.082
-JUST DON'T DIP OUT OF
YOUR DRESS AND EMBARRASS ME.

24:35.212 --> 24:36.431
-WO-HOO!

24:40.174 --> 24:44.483
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

24:55.319 --> 24:58.192
-RON! RON, DON'T DO THIS!

24:58.322 --> 25:00.455
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]

25:00.586 --> 25:02.283
-DON'T WORRY, I'M NOT
PLANNING ON DROWNING.

25:02.413 --> 25:04.981
-OH, THAT'S GOOD BECAUSE I'M
NOT PLANNING ON LETTING YOU.

25:05.982 --> 25:07.157
-YOU'RE NOT MY GUARDIAN ANGEL.

25:07.288 --> 25:08.681
-NO, I'M NOT.

25:09.290 --> 25:11.814
I'M A LIFEGUARD AND
I'M NOT GONNA WATCH YOU

25:11.945 --> 25:13.424
THROW YOUR LIFE AWAY JUST
BECAUSE YOU DON'T HAVE

25:13.555 --> 25:14.948
THE SAME ATHLETIC PROWESS
THAT YOU ONCE DID.

25:15.775 --> 25:17.428
THERE'S MORE TO LIVE FOR.

25:18.081 --> 25:19.605
-NOT FOR ME.

25:19.735 --> 25:21.998
-HEY, IF YOU'RE SO PISSED
OFF ABOUT THE POLITICS

25:22.129 --> 25:24.261
OF AIDS RESEARCH, WHY DON'T
YOU GET INVOLVED INSTEAD

25:24.392 --> 25:25.872
OF STANDING AROUND
AND BITCHING ABOUT IT.

25:26.002 --> 25:28.091
-BECAUSE I'M NOT UP THEIR
ASS AND I'M NOT MAGIC.

25:29.353 --> 25:30.833
I'M THE PERSON
PEOPLE LOVE TO HATE.

25:31.486 --> 25:35.446
THAT WAS MY REPUTATION AND
WHETHER I'M HERE OR NOT

25:35.577 --> 25:36.970
IS NOT GONNA MAKE A
DIFFERENCE TO ANYBODY.

25:37.579 --> 25:38.885
-RON, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

25:40.060 --> 25:41.496
-I'LL MAKE IT.

25:51.680 --> 25:56.946
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

26:16.618 --> 26:18.751
-HI, THIS IS
CAROLINE, TOWER ONE.

26:19.578 --> 26:21.754
I'VE GOT A BOAT DRIFTING
IN THE SURF LINE HERE.

26:21.884 --> 26:25.540
IT COULD CAPSIZE AND I'VE GOT
A SWIMMER I'VE GOTTA BRING IN.

26:27.411 --> 26:29.065
ALL RIGHT, THANKS.

28:31.840 --> 28:34.321
-[WATER CRASHING]

28:34.451 --> 28:36.627
-[SCREAMING]

28:50.685 --> 28:54.036
GRAB THE CAN, A BOAT'S CAPSIZED,
I HAVE TO GO HELP THEM.

28:54.167 --> 28:55.646
HOLD ON!

29:12.098 --> 29:16.493
-[SIRENS WAILING]

29:38.254 --> 29:39.212
HEY, YOU OKAY?

29:39.342 --> 29:40.866
-HURRY UP, MY WIFE!

29:42.998 --> 29:44.652
-I GOT HER, I GOT HER.

29:46.001 --> 29:48.525
ALL RIGHT, SHE'S UNCONSCIOUS,
SHE'S UNCONSCIOUS. I GOT YOU.

29:51.354 --> 29:53.095
-LET'S GET THEM OUT OF HERE!

29:54.923 --> 29:57.447
-OKAY, GET HIM. GET HIM.

29:57.578 --> 29:59.145
-I GOT YOU.

30:04.063 --> 30:07.718
-RON: WE'RE GONNA GO ON
THREE. ONE, TWO, THREE!

30:28.914 --> 30:30.176
-MAN: YEAH, I'LL TAKE IT.

30:31.742 --> 30:33.396
REAL SOON, I'M GOING BACK TO HQ.

30:50.457 --> 30:52.285
-YOU SAID THAT WHETHER
YOU WERE HERE OR NOT

30:52.415 --> 30:54.200
WOULDN'T MAKE A
DIFFERENCE TO ANYBODY.

30:55.766 --> 30:56.942
YOU MADE THE BIGGEST DIFFERENCE

30:57.072 --> 30:58.682
THAT ANYBODY COULD EVER MAKE.

30:59.770 --> 31:01.511
YOU SAVED A LIFE.

31:03.513 --> 31:04.819
-SO DID YOU.

31:14.089 --> 31:15.308
THANKS.

31:26.972 --> 31:28.625
-MAN: WILL ALL
DANCERS PARTICIPATING

31:28.756 --> 31:30.671
IN THE COMPETITION PLEASE
HAVE A COPY OF YOUR MUSIC

31:30.801 --> 31:32.716
READY TO SUBMIT TO THE JUDGES.

31:32.847 --> 31:34.631
THE COMPETITION WILL BEGIN IN--

31:34.762 --> 31:37.939
-I THOUGHT C.J. SAID EVERYBODY
WAS WEARING DRESS UNIFORMS.

31:39.941 --> 31:42.248
-DID SHE? I DON'T KNOW,
I WASN'T THERE, REMEMBER?

32:12.713 --> 32:17.631
-[SMOOTH, RELAXING MUSIC]

32:17.761 --> 32:20.155
-I'M GONNA USE WHAT
HOBIE'S DOING AS INSPIRATION

32:20.286 --> 32:21.722
FOR MY DANCE.

32:21.852 --> 32:23.245
-WELL, THEN IT'S GOING
TO BE A DISASTER BECAUSE

32:23.376 --> 32:25.204
THAT'S THE WAY THESE
THINGS ALWAYS END UP.

32:25.334 --> 32:26.770
-WELL, THINK NEGATIVE
IF YOU WANT TO,

32:26.901 --> 32:29.512
BUT I HAPPEN TO BELIEVE
IN HAPPY ENDINGS.

32:29.643 --> 32:34.343
-C.J., TINA AND I
GOT BACK TOGETHER.

32:34.474 --> 32:35.431
SORRY.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.565
I DON'T MIND, IT'S
ABOUT WINNING.

32:39.218 --> 32:40.959
-WELL, I FEEL SORRY FOR
YOU THEN BECAUSE IT SHOULD

32:41.089 --> 32:42.438
BE ABOUT DANCING.

32:46.616 --> 32:48.444
-OH, C.J. I'M SORRY.

32:50.229 --> 32:51.970
-[CRYING]

32:57.627 --> 32:59.455
-COME ON, DAD, JUST
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

32:59.586 --> 33:01.980
-HALF HOUR OF GOING
IN CIRCLES IS MY LIMIT.

33:02.110 --> 33:03.372
-COME ON, FIVE MINUTES.

33:03.503 --> 33:05.548
-SORRY, PAL, NATURE CALLS.

33:06.201 --> 33:08.508
-ALL RIGHT, WELL, I'LL KEEP
RIDING UNTIL YOU GET BACK.

33:29.572 --> 33:32.358
-EXCUSE ME-- EXCUSE
ME. OH, I'M SORRY THERE.

33:32.488 --> 33:33.315
WAIT A SECOND.

33:33.446 --> 33:34.273
-NO, IT WAS MY FAULT.

33:34.403 --> 33:35.883
-GET YOUR STUFF HERE.

33:36.536 --> 33:39.060
SORRY, AMERICAN AIRLINES
TICKET. DON'T WANT

33:39.191 --> 33:40.148
TO FORGET THAT, HUH?

33:40.279 --> 33:41.802
-THANKS.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.893
YOU'RE HOBIE'S DAD, AREN'T YOU?

33:46.024 --> 33:46.850
-YEAH, YEAH.

33:46.981 --> 33:48.809
-I'M CALLIE.

33:48.939 --> 33:50.680
-I'M MITCH BUCHANNON.

33:51.725 --> 33:53.205
YOU ONE OF HOBIE'S TEACHERS?

33:53.335 --> 33:55.511
-NO, I'M THE FRIEND HE
MET THROUGH THE RADIO.

33:56.251 --> 33:57.687
HE'S TOLD ME A LOT ABOUT YOU.

33:57.818 --> 33:59.167
-[LAUGHING]

33:59.298 --> 34:01.256
WOULD YOU EXCUSE
ME JUST FOR A SECOND?

34:01.387 --> 34:03.867
I GOTTA THROW MY SON OFF THE
TOP OF THAT FERRIS WHEEL.

34:04.477 --> 34:07.132
-YOU'RE LUCKY TO HAVE A
SON WHO LOVES YOU SO MUCH.

34:07.741 --> 34:09.090
COULD WE GO SOMEWHERE AND TALK?

34:09.786 --> 34:11.527
-I JUST WANTED TO DANCE.

34:12.527 --> 34:15.226
-I KNOW. C.J., EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

34:15.357 --> 34:17.880
-YOU GUYS, CALLIE HASN'T SHOWN
UP YET AND I DON'T KNOW

34:18.012 --> 34:19.318
WHERE DAD IS.

34:19.447 --> 34:21.275
I THINK HE MIGHT'VE LEFT.

34:21.407 --> 34:23.757
-[CRYING]

34:29.458 --> 34:32.331
-AFTER JESSIE DIED OF AIDS,
I WAS ANGRY AT THE WORLD

34:33.418 --> 34:34.594
ESPECIALLY AT THE
PEOPLE WHO WERE TRYING

34:34.724 --> 34:36.204
TO HELP ME THROUGH IT.

34:37.422 --> 34:39.554
FOR SOME REASON, I THOUGHT
I HAD TO HOLD ON TO THE PAIN

34:39.686 --> 34:41.775
IN ORDER TO HOLD
ON TO THE MEMORY.

34:43.733 --> 34:45.126
BUT THAT WASN'T TRUE.

34:46.562 --> 34:47.955
-HOW'D YOU GET OVER IT?

34:48.521 --> 34:52.699
-I LET LOVE BACK INTO MY LIFE,
INTO MY WORK, INTO MY HEART.

34:54.701 --> 34:56.964
THERE ARE A LOT OF PEOPLE
WHO LOVE US, MITCH.

34:57.530 --> 34:59.575
OUR FRIENDS, OUR FAMILY.

35:00.315 --> 35:03.971
-YEAH.
-THEIR LOVE CAN SEE US
THROUGH UNTIL THAT OTHER KIND

35:04.102 --> 35:06.800
OF SPECIAL LOVE
COMES ALONG AGAIN.

35:08.106 --> 35:09.281
-YEAH.

35:10.717 --> 35:12.719
IF IT EVER DOES COME AGAIN.

35:14.460 --> 35:15.852
-I THINK IT WILL.

35:16.418 --> 35:19.291
IN TIME IF WE'RE OPEN TO IT.

35:21.989 --> 35:24.905
-COME ON, I'D LIKE
YOU TO MEET SOME

35:25.035 --> 35:26.515
OF MY FAMILY AND FRIENDS.

35:26.646 --> 35:27.951
-LOVE TO.

35:29.779 --> 35:34.523
-[DANCE MUSIC]

35:51.410 --> 35:55.327
-I HOPE HE TRIPS ON HER DRESS
AND BITES OFF HIS TONGUE.

35:55.457 --> 35:57.459
-HI, HOBIE, I'M CALLIE.

35:57.590 --> 35:59.766
-HI, IT'S GREAT TO
FINALLY MEET YOU.

36:00.419 --> 36:02.769
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?
HOW'D YOU GUYS MEET UP?

36:02.899 --> 36:04.988
-WE RAN INTO EACH OTHER.

36:05.902 --> 36:09.123
WE LITERALLY RAN INTO EACH
OTHER ON THE WAY HERE.

36:10.298 --> 36:11.256
COME ON.

36:13.345 --> 36:16.391
CALLIE, I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET
TWO VERY CLOSE FRIENDS OF MINE.

36:16.522 --> 36:17.958
C.J., STEPHANIE, THIS IS CALLIE.

36:18.088 --> 36:20.700
-HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.
THAT'S A GREAT T-SHIRT.

36:20.830 --> 36:22.658
-OH, THANKS, IT'S A
NEW WAY I'M THINKING

36:22.789 --> 36:24.443
OF EXPOSING PEOPLE TO ART.

36:24.573 --> 36:25.357
-WOW.

36:25.487 --> 36:27.402
-HI, I'M C.J.

36:27.533 --> 36:29.361
AT LEAST SOMEBODY'S
HAVING A HAPPY ENDING.

36:29.491 --> 36:30.927
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

36:32.015 --> 36:33.669
-C.J.'S DANCE PARTNER DUMPED
HER AT THE LAST MINUTE.

36:33.800 --> 36:35.758
-YOU'RE KIDDING ME. OH.

36:36.281 --> 36:38.979
-NOW HE'S DANCING WITH
HIS EX-DANCE PARTNER.

36:46.987 --> 36:48.075
-COME ON.

36:56.257 --> 36:59.129
-WHOA, I DON'T THINK
THEY PLANNED THAT STEP.
-CONCENTRATE, GET UP! COME ON!

36:59.260 --> 37:00.914
-THAT'S IT!

37:02.045 --> 37:03.960
-YOU MEAN EX, EX-DANCE PARTNER.

37:04.091 --> 37:06.224
-WELL, THEY DESERVE EACH OTHER.

37:06.963 --> 37:09.096
-CALLIE: LOOKS LIKE YOU
HAVE A FRIEND IN NEED, MITCH.

37:09.966 --> 37:13.622
-WELL, YOU STILL WANNA ENTER
THE CONTEST, GINGER ROGERS?

37:14.319 --> 37:15.885
-WELL, I DON'T HAVE
MY FRED ASTAIRE.

37:16.016 --> 37:17.800
-NO, BUT YOU GOT
MITCH BUCHANNON.

37:17.931 --> 37:20.542
AND I AM YOUR FAVORITE
DANCE PARTNER, REMEMBER?

37:31.901 --> 37:37.472
-[SLOW MUSIC]

37:48.309 --> 37:51.878
-[APPLAUSE]

38:04.020 --> 38:06.327
[APPLAUSE]

38:16.990 --> 38:19.427
-[LAUGHING]

38:26.216 --> 38:30.264
-[APPLAUSE]

38:45.540 --> 38:46.454
-MITCH: CHECK IT OUT!

38:46.585 --> 38:49.414
-[LAUGHING]

38:49.544 --> 38:50.893
-MAN: WO-HOO!

38:55.333 --> 38:57.552
-[LAUGHING]

38:59.554 --> 39:04.864
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

39:10.173 --> 39:11.218
-HI.

39:13.263 --> 39:14.264
-HI.

39:15.570 --> 39:16.789
-WHAT ARE YOU READING?

39:18.660 --> 39:19.966
-A LETTER FROM RON.

39:21.228 --> 39:23.709
HE'S GONE HOME TO
BE WITH HIS FAMILY.

39:24.884 --> 39:26.364
HE SAID HE'S GONNA
SEND ME A PHOTOGRAPH

39:26.494 --> 39:28.496
OF ALL OF THEM TOGETHER.

39:30.542 --> 39:31.456
-GOOD.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.726
-SO, WHY DO YOU HAVE
YOUR CAN WITH YOU?

39:40.856 --> 39:41.988
-I'M GLAD YOU ASKED.

39:42.815 --> 39:45.252
IT'S MY REDESIGN. THE
ONE I'VE BEEN WORKING ON.

39:45.383 --> 39:47.733
THE POCKET MASK
FITS RIGHT IN HERE,

39:48.342 --> 39:49.735
SO IT'S ALWAYS THERE
IF YOU NEED IT.

39:50.692 --> 39:52.346
-THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

39:55.218 --> 39:56.698
IT'S A GREAT IDEA,
LOGAN, IT REALLY IS.

39:56.829 --> 40:01.703
-I FIGURED, YOU KNOW,
HEY, SAFE SEX, SAFE CPR.

40:06.012 --> 40:09.145
I AM REALLY SORRY ABOUT THE
WAY I ACTED THE OTHER NIGHT.

40:11.191 --> 40:12.366
-ME, TOO.

40:13.149 --> 40:18.546
-[CALMING MUSIC]

40:35.824 --> 40:38.261
-YOU KNOW, DAD, I THINK THESE

40:38.392 --> 40:39.698
ARE MY FAVORITE TIMES TOGETHER.

40:39.828 --> 40:41.917
JUST ME AND YOU
WALKING ON THE BEACH.

40:42.918 --> 40:45.094
-WE'VE BEEN DOING IT FOR
A LOT OF YEARS, HAVEN'T WE?

40:45.747 --> 40:49.229
-YEAH. I HOPE WE NEVER STOP.

40:49.359 --> 40:50.709
-ME, TOO, PAL.

40:53.059 --> 40:54.887
-YOU KNOW, NOW
THAT I THINK OF IT,

40:56.454 --> 40:58.630
FOR A LONG TIME, YOU'VE
BEEN CALLING ME PAL,

40:58.760 --> 40:59.935
EVEN THOUGH I'M YOUR SON.

41:00.632 --> 41:02.068
WHY IS THAT?

41:03.112 --> 41:04.462
-WELL, I GUESS
IT'S 'CAUSE I THINK

41:04.592 --> 41:06.333
OF YOU AS MY BEST FRIEND TOO.

41:06.899 --> 41:09.467
-WOW, THAT'S PRETTY COOL.

41:11.381 --> 41:13.296
SO, ARE YOU GONNA
SEE CALLIE AGAIN?

41:13.427 --> 41:16.561
-MITCH: SURE, SHE'S
BECOME A GOOD FRIEND, PAL.

41:16.691 --> 41:19.302
EVERYONE NEEDS HELP FROM
THEIR FRIENDS NOW AND THEN.

41:21.391 --> 41:23.132
-I LOVE YOU, DAD.

41:24.917 --> 41:26.484
I LOVE YOU A LOT.

41:26.614 --> 41:29.269
-I LOVE YOU, TOO, PAL. [LAUGHS]

41:29.399 --> 41:30.488
SON.

41:36.363 --> 41:39.105
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
